To obtain gene regulatory interactions and reconstruct gene network (Fig. 1c) from gene perturbation experiments, we developed a computational pipeline, which is divided into several steps. The z-scored perturbation expression profiles are represented as Zj∈Z with j = 1,…,n, in our case n=591. Each profile Zj comprises mj biological replicates (usually between 2 and 4), which are repeated measurements of biologically distinct samples and capture random biological variation [14]. Each biological replicate is the average of qk technical replicates, which are repeated measurements of the same sample (usually between 4 and 6). A given perturbation experiment is represented as: 
